law.text:
At least once every thirty (30) days, the supervising authority shall provide all local and county law enforcement agencies with a list of the offenders under home incarceration in their jurisdictions. This list shall include the following information:
The prisoner's place of home incarceration;
The crime for which the prisoner was convicted;
The date that the sentence of home incarceration will be completed; and
The name, address and phone number of the officer of the authority supervising the prisoner.
